{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"layoutPriority"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"value"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The priority by which a parent layout apportions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space to the child."}]}],"name":"value"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Views typically have a default priority of ","type":"text"},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which causes space to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"apportioned evenly to all sibling views. Raising a view’s layout","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"priority encourages the higher priority view to shrink later when the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group is shrunk and stretch sooner when the group is stretched.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HStack {","    Text(\"This is a moderately long string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .border(Color.gray)","","    Spacer()","","    Text(\"This is a higher priority string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .layoutPriority(1)","        .border(Color.gray)","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example above, the first "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" element has the default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"priority "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":" which causes its view to shrink dramatically due to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"higher priority of the second "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text"},{"type":"text","text":" element, even though all of their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other attributes (font, font size and character count) are the same."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A parent layout offers the child views with the highest layout priority","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"all the space offered to the parent minus the minimum space required for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"all its lower-priority children.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"platforms":[{"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","remoteSource":{"fileName":"LayoutPriority.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources